Lets look into other tags...<br> a B tag bolds just like a strong tag<br>
a Big tag makes test big IE. <big> BIG </big> <br>
a Small tag makes text small IE. <small> small </small><br>
a S tag strikes through text IE. <s> Strike through </s><br>
</p>

<h4> Making a "Form" </h4>

<p> A form tag make a "form" to start an input, This will start an area to put the input this cannot be shown so the example is "away" from the paragraph text ie. <form>Form Starts Here</form><br>
<br>
An A tag is a link tag, It is all the links on a page (In part 3 we I will show you how to style it.)<br>
It looks like this without the angle brackets.. <br>
a href="http://www.Website.com">Visit Website.com! /a <br>
The herf is how you definen the link, the secound part is what the link will say! IE.<br>
<a href="http://www.pandanetworks.net">Visit PandaNetworks.net!</a><br>
<br>
This is where it gets <b>CONFUSING</b> So pay attention...<br>
The next step is an input tag, without the angle brackets it looks like this<br>
input type="" name="" value=""<br>
the type can be set to a ...	
</p>
<big>
<b>
<ul>
